:vsplit -- split vertically
C-(g,h,j,k) -- navigate to different tab
u -- undo
p -- paste
"0p -- paste from 0 registery
i -- insert
dnd -- delete n rows below
dd -- delete line
yy -- yank /copy line
e -- move forword to the end of line
w -- move forward to the start of line
A -- insert at the end of the line
TEXT -------------
a] arround [...]
i] inner [...]

Ctrl - ++ zoom

:%s/foo/bar/gc --Change each 'foo' to 'bar', but ask for confirmation first.

ya] --- yank around[...] 
o	Begin a new line below the cursor
O	Begin a new line above the cursor
r{text}	Replace the character under the cursor with {text}
R	Replace characters instead of inserting them

Ctrl-y Moves screen up one line
Ctrl-e Moves screen down one line
Ctrl-u Moves cursor & screen up ½ page
Ctrl-d Moves cursor & screen down ½ page
Ctrl-b Moves screen up one page, cursor to last line
Ctrl-f Moves screen down one page, cursor to first line


zz - move current line to the middle of the screen
(Careful with zz, if you happen to have Caps Lock on accidentally, you will save and exit vim!)
zt - move current line to the top of the screen
zb - move current line to the bottom of the screen

:colo tab --change color Scheme 
SURROUND ////////////////////
ysiw) = add surrounging inner word () // surroung word with ()
